parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall without warning, and experience power steering failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls without warning
the power steering shuts off
the vehicle comes to a complete stop
the check engine and traction control warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for recall repairs can cause inconvenience to the vehicle owner and may lead to safety issues if the recall is related to a critical system.
symptoms: The contact is unable to schedule a recall repair due to parts unavailability
the contact is told to wait for an extended period for parts to arrive
the contact experiences frustration and inconvenience.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the vehicle loses power
the power steering shuts off
the vehicle comes to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dashboard Defect and Airbag Assembly Concern
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lifting and bubbling of the passenger side dashboard can cause a serious safety hazard, potentially affecting the airbag assembly and its functionality.
symptoms: The dashboard lifts from its mounting
bubbles up
and waffles across the top
migrating towards the airbag assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Cable Chafing and Electrical Short
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The chafing of the battery cable can cause an electrical short, leading to a potential fire hazard or loss of vehicle functionality.
symptoms: None reported
as this is a recall notice (NHTSA 19V-809).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of carbon monoxide into the cabin can cause serious health risks, including headaches, dizziness, and even death.
symptoms: Carbon monoxide levels in the cabin increase during highway driving
especially when climbing grades
and decrease when windows are opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of exhaust gases into the cabin can cause serious health risks, including headaches, dizziness, and even death.
symptoms: Strong smell of exhaust leakage or rotten eggs in the passenger cabin
which becomes stronger as vehicle speed increases
especially when the air conditioning is in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the rear brake hose can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of braking performance, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid warning light is illuminated
brake fluid leaking from the rear brake lines
brake pedal has to be manually raised to the normal upright position
vehicle fails to come to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Rear Brake Hose
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed availability of parts for the recall repair can leave vehicles with a potentially faulty rear brake hose, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the delay in receiving the recall repair.
